*Use case:* search for Issues created on a specific date.

For a lot of users, it's intuitive that a query like:
{noformat}
createdDate = <date>
{noformat}
will return all Issues created in that day's span. However, as stated in the documentation:
{quote}if a time-component is not specified, midnight will be assumed.{quote}
That means that the query above would only return Issues created exactly at midnight. A query to retrieve all Issues created on a certain date has to specify the hours between midnights:
{noformat}
created < "2013-08-05 23:59" and created > "2013-08-05 00:00"
{noformat}

It would be less confusing if the _createdDate_ field reference assumed the span of the whole day, especially as its name mentions "date".

